On 4/15/04 7:58 AM, "incynr8" <incynr8(-at-)lawngnome.org> wrote:

> Also consider removing the finish around the lug bolt seating area to
> allow for proper torque against the rim. This would be a solution if
> thick coating or powdercoast is used.

The problem here is beware of powder coaters and give them instructions. A
good one should be masking bores and threads and putting those little nubs
in the welded on nuts, etc otherwise you'll have a really difficult time
getting things back together.

